Thank you for your interest in Sacramento State!


This articulation agreement displays the lower-division courses required in the major: Sacramento State courses on the left and approved (articulated) transfer courses on the right. Although completion of the coursework listed below is not mandatory prior to admission, students are advised to complete as much lower-division course preparation as possible prior to transfer.


Additional Resources:

  • See the University Catalog for the full listing of degree requirements for this major.
  • Visit our Sac State Apply page for more information about our campus!
  • Visit the Admissions website for current transfer admission requirements.
  • Connect with an Admissions Counselor.

templateAssets.content:
1. Students must earn a "C-" grade or higher in all courses required in the major.
  2. Foreign Language Graduation Requirement Exemption: Students graduating with a B.S. in Construction Management will not be subject to the University's Foreign Language Graduation Requirement. Students who change major may be subject to the University's Foreign Language Graduation Requirement.
  3. Please contact a Construction Management advisor for details of requirements and procedures to be admitted, and for a list of the special General Education requirements that apply to this major. Construction Management majors are required to see an advisor once each semester.
  4. Construction Management Majors may qualify for certain exemptions from General Education requirements. Please contact a Sacramento State Construction Management Advisor for details. The following courses may also be used to satisfy General Education: COMS 4 or 5; ECON 1A or 1B; ENGL 5; ENVS 10; MATH 26A, 26B; PHYS 5A, 5B; STAT 1.
  5. All Construction Management Majors will be required to demonstrate computer literacy and competency prior to enrolling in upper-division courses.
  6. Construction Management Majors also earn a Minor in Business Administration in addition to their Bachelor of Science in Construction Management. Students must declare their Minor in the College of Business (Students must complete the following before applying for the minor: ACCY 1, 2; STAT 1). CM transfers should contact an advisor in the Undergraduate Business Advising Center in the College of Business at (916) 278-6771 for further instructions.
  7. For additional information, please visit: Department of Construction Management.
